  1: # Refactoring UpdateEventHandler.recurring.test.ts with Doppler
  2: 
  3: ## Overview
  4: 
  5: Instead of testing a shadow implementation, we'll refactor `UpdateEventHandler.recurring.test.ts` to:
  6: 1. Use real `UpdateEventHandler` and `RecurringEventHelpers` from source
  7: 2. Load real Google OAuth credentials from Doppler
  8: 3. Test actual Google Calendar API interactions
  9: 4. Run with `npm run test:integration:doppler`
 10: 
 11: ## Current State
 12: 
 13: **File:** `src/tests/unit/handlers/UpdateEventHandler.recurring.test.ts`
 14: 
 15: **Problems:**
 16: - Tests a fake `EnhancedUpdateEventHandler` class (lines 6–199)
 17: - Wrong scope values: `'single'` vs `'thisEventOnly'`, `'future'` vs `'thisAndFollowing'`
 18: - Cannot catch regressions in real handler
 19: - No error code validation
 20: 
 21: ## Proposed Refactor
 22: 
 23: ### Step 1: Move to Integration Tests
 24: 
 25: ```bash
 26: mv src/tests/unit/handlers/UpdateEventHandler.recurring.test.ts \
 27:    src/tests/integration/UpdateEventHandler.recurring.test.ts
 28: ```
 29: 
 30: Rationale: Integration tests expect real credentials and run against real APIs.
 31: 
 32: ### Step 2: Import Real Handler
 33: 
 34: ```typescript
 35: // BEFORE (shadow class)
 36: class EnhancedUpdateEventHandler { /* ... */ }
 37: 
 38: // AFTER (real handler)
 39: import { UpdateEventHandler } from '../../../handlers/core/UpdateEventHandler.js';
 40: import { RecurringEventHelpers } from '../../../handlers/core/RecurringEventHelpers.js';
 41: import { OAuth2Client } from 'google-auth-library';
 42: import { initializeOAuth2Client } from '../../../auth/client.js';
 43: import { TokenManager } from '../../../auth/tokenManager.js';
 44: ```
 45: 
 46: ### Step 3: Setup Real OAuth Client
 47: 
 48: ```typescript
 49: describe('UpdateEventHandler - Recurring Events', () => {
 50:   let handler: UpdateEventHandler;
 51:   let oauth2Client: OAuth2Client;
 52: 
 53:   beforeAll(async () => {
 54:     // Load real credentials from Doppler
 55:     oauth2Client = await initializeOAuth2Client();
 56:     const tokenManager = new TokenManager(oauth2Client);
 57:     const hasValidTokens = await tokenManager.validateTokens();
 58: 
 59:     if (!hasValidTokens) {
 60:       throw new Error('No valid tokens found. Run: npm run auth');
 61:     }
 62:   });
 63: 
 64:   beforeEach(() => {
 65:     handler = new UpdateEventHandler();
 66:   });
 67: 
 68:   afterAll(async () => {
 69:     // Optional: cleanup
 70:   });
 71: });
 72: ```
 73: 
 74: ### Step 4: Replace Mock-Based Tests with Real API Tests
 75: 
 76: **BEFORE (mock-based, wrong scope values):**
 77: ```typescript
 78: it('should detect event type and route to appropriate method', async () => {
 79:   const recurringEvent = {
 80:     data: {
 81:       id: 'recurring123',
 82:       summary: 'Weekly Meeting',
 83:       recurrence: ['RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;BYDAY=MO']
 84:     }
 85:   };
 86:   mockCalendar.events.get.mockResolvedValue(recurringEvent);
 87:   mockCalendar.events.patch.mockResolvedValue({ data: recurringEvent.data });
 88: 
 89:   const args = {
 90:     calendarId: 'primary',
 91:     eventId: 'recurring123',
 92:     timeZone: 'America/Los_Angeles',
 93:     modificationScope: 'all', // ← shadow uses this, not needed for 'all'
 94:     summary: 'Updated Meeting'
 95:   };
 96: 
 97:   await handler.updateEventWithScope(args);
 98:   expect(mockCalendar.events.patch).toHaveBeenCalled();
 99: });
100: ```
101: 
102: **AFTER (real API test, correct scope values):**
103: ```typescript
104: it('should update all instances of a recurring event', async () => {
105:   // 1. Create a test recurring event
106:   const testEvent = {
107:     summary: 'Test Recurring - Update All',
108:     description: 'Integration test event',
109:     start: { dateTime: new Date(Date.now() + 86400000).toISOString(), timeZone: 'UTC' },
110:     end: { dateTime: new Date(Date.now() + 90000000).toISOString(), timeZone: 'UTC' },
111:     recurrence: ['RRULE:FREQ=DAILY;COUNT=5']
112:   };
113: 
114:   const calendar = new google.calendar_v3.Calendar({ auth: oauth2Client });
115:   const createResp = await calendar.events.insert({
116:     calendarId: 'primary',
117:     requestBody: testEvent
118:   });
119:   const eventId = createResp.data.id!;
120: 
121:   // 2. Update all instances with correct scope
122:   const result = await handler.runTool({
123:     calendarId: 'primary',
124:     eventId: eventId,
125:     modificationScope: 'all', // ← correct value
126:     summary: 'Updated Recurring Event',
127:     timeZone: 'UTC'
128:   }, oauth2Client);
129: 
130:   // 3. Assert on real response format
131:   expect(result.content[0].type).toBe('text');
132:   expect(result.content[0].text).toContain('Updated Recurring Event');
133: 
134:   // 4. Cleanup
135:   await calendar.events.delete({
136:     calendarId: 'primary',
137:     eventId: eventId
138:   });
139: });
140: ```
141: 
142: ### Step 5: Add Tests for Real Error Codes
143: 
144: ```typescript
145: it('should throw RecurringEventError when using thisEventOnly on non-recurring event', async () => {
146:   // 1. Create a single (non-recurring) event
147:   const testEvent = {
148:     summary: 'Single Event',
149:     start: { dateTime: new Date(Date.now() + 86400000).toISOString(), timeZone: 'UTC' },
150:     end: { dateTime: new Date(Date.now() + 90000000).toISOString(), timeZone: 'UTC' }
151:   };
152: 
153:   const calendar = new google.calendar_v3.Calendar({ auth: oauth2Client });
154:   const createResp = await calendar.events.insert({
155:     calendarId: 'primary',
156:     requestBody: testEvent
157:   });
158:   const eventId = createResp.data.id!;
159: 
160:   // 2. Try to use thisEventOnly on single event
161:   await expect(handler.runTool({
162:     calendarId: 'primary',
163:     eventId: eventId,
164:     modificationScope: 'thisEventOnly', // ← correct value, should error
165:     originalStartTime: new Date().toISOString(),
166:     summary: 'Updated'
167:   }, oauth2Client)).rejects.toThrow('Scope other than "all" only applies to recurring events');
168: 
169:   // 3. Cleanup
170:   await calendar.events.delete({
171:     calendarId: 'primary',
172:     eventId: eventId
173:   });
174: });
175: ```
176: 
177: ### Step 6: Test All Modification Scopes
178: 
179: ```typescript
180: describe('modificationScope behavior', () => {
181:   let testEventId: string;
182: 
183:   beforeAll(async () => {
184:     // Create recurring test event
185:     const calendar = new google.calendar_v3.Calendar({ auth: oauth2Client });
186:     const resp = await calendar.events.insert({
187:       calendarId: 'primary',
188:       requestBody: {
189:         summary: 'Scope Test Event',
190:         recurrence: ['RRULE:FREQ=DAILY;COUNT=10'],
191:         start: { dateTime: new Date(Date.now() + 86400000).toISOString(), timeZone: 'UTC' },
192:         end: { dateTime: new Date(Date.now() + 90000000).toISOString(), timeZone: 'UTC' }
193:       }
194:     });
195:     testEventId = resp.data.id!;
196:   });
197: 
198:   it('should update all instances with scope "all"', async () => {
199:     const result = await handler.runTool({
200:       calendarId: 'primary',
201:       eventId: testEventId,
202:       modificationScope: 'all',
203:       summary: 'All Updated'
204:     }, oauth2Client);
205: 
206:     expect(result.content[0].text).toContain('All Updated');
207:   });
208: 
209:   it('should update single instance with scope "thisEventOnly"', async () => {
210:     const now = new Date();
211:     const result = await handler.runTool({
212:       calendarId: 'primary',
213:       eventId: testEventId,
214:       modificationScope: 'thisEventOnly',
215:       originalStartTime: now.toISOString(),
216:       summary: 'Single Instance Updated'
217:     }, oauth2Client);
