261: ## 💡 Key Insights
262: 
263: ### Timezone Handling
264: The biggest implementation detail is timezone conversion:
265: - Google Calendar: `{ dateTime: "2026-03-24T10:00", timeZone: "America/Los_Angeles" }`
266: - Schema.org Event: `startDate: "2026-03-24T10:00:00-07:00"` (ISO 8601 with offset)
267: 
268: **Solution**: Convert timeZone + dateTime to ISO 8601 with UTC offset
269: 
270: ### RSVP Status
271: Google Calendar uses `responseStatus` on attendees:
272: - Accepted, Declined, Tentative, NeedsAction
273: 
274: **Schema.org Solution**: Use Reservation type with `reservationStatus`:
275: - ReservationConfirmed, ReservationPending, ReservationCancelled
276: 
277: ### Custom Extensions
278: Conflict detection (ConflictInfo, DuplicateInfo) don't have schema.org equivalents:
279: - Option A: Create custom `@type: ConflictInfo` extension
280: - Option B: Add custom properties to Event object
281: - **Recommended**: Option A (cleaner separation)
