262: ## 🎯 Key Recommendations
263: 
264: ### DO ✅
265: - Use ISO 8601 datetime format (schema.org standard)
266: - Include `@context: https://schema.org` in examples
267: - Map all human-readable fields (name, email, title)
268: - Use standard types before creating custom extensions
269: - Document timezone handling explicitly
270: - Generate examples with `generate_example` tool
271: - Validate with https://validator.schema.org/
272: 
273: ### DON'T ❌
274: - Use custom field names without schema.org properties
275: - Mix timezone representations
276: - Omit required properties (name, startDate for Events)
277: - Create custom types for standard concepts
278: - Hardcode timezone offsets
279: - Forget to include @context in JSON-LD
