  1: # Architecture Overview
  2: 
  3: ## High-Level Flow
  4: 
  5: ```
  6: CLI Entry (index.ts)
  7:   ↓
  8: GoogleCalendarMcpServer (server.ts)
  9:   ├─ Authentication (auth/)
 10:   │  ├─ OAuth2Client init
 11:   │  ├─ TokenManager (multi-account, auto-refresh)
 12:   │  └─ AuthServer (browser flow)
 13:   ├─ ToolRegistry (tools/registry.ts)
 14:   │  └─ Handler dispatch
 15:   └─ Transport (transports/)
 16:      ├─ Stdio (Claude Desktop)
 17:      └─ HTTP (remote access)
 18: ```
 19: 
 20: ## Directory Structure
 21: 
 22: ### `src/auth/`
 23: - **client.ts** - OAuth2Client initialization with credentials validation
 24: - **tokenManager.ts** - Multi-account token lifecycle with TokenManager API:
 25:   - `isAuthenticated()` - Check valid, non-expired token status
 26:   - `getCredentials()` - Access current account credentials
 27:   - `refreshCredentials()` - Explicit token refresh
 28:   - `logout()` - Clear tokens for account
 29:   - Auto-refresh 5 min before expiry, account-aware storage
 30: - **server.ts** - OAuth browser flow for authentication
 31: - **utils.ts** - Token parsing, credential loading helpers
 32: 
 33: ### `src/handlers/core/`
 34: Implements MCP tool handlers via `BaseToolHandler` pattern:
 35: - **ListEventsHandler** - Multi-calendar event listing with date filtering
 36: - **CreateEventHandler** - Event creation with recurring event support
 37: - **UpdateEventHandler** - Event updates with field mask optimization
 38: - **DeleteEventHandler** - Event deletion with conflict detection
 39: - **SearchEventsHandler** - Text-based event search
 40: - **FreeBusyHandler** - Cross-calendar availability checks
 41: - **ListColorsHandler** - Event color palette
 42: - **GetCurrentTimeHandler** - Server time (timezone-aware)
 43: - **RecurringEventHelpers** - Shared logic for recurring event modifications
 44: - **BatchRequestHandler** - Batch Gmail operations
 45: 
 46: ### `src/handlers/gmail/`
 47: Gmail-specific handlers:
 48: - **GmailSearchHandler** - Message search with filter syntax
 49: - **GmailModifyHandler** - Batch operations (mark read/archive/delete/label)
 50: - **GmailCreateHandler** - Label and filter creation
 51: 
 52: ### `src/services/`
 53: Business logic (conflicts, event similarity):
 54: - **ConflictDetectionService** - Time-based overlap detection
 55: - **EventSimilarityService** - Fuzzy event matching
 56: 
 57: ### `src/utils/`
 58: Shared utilities:
 59: - **timezone-utils.ts** - RFC3339 conversion, timezone offset calculation, datetime object construction
 60: - **date-utils.ts** - Date parsing and validation
 61: - **field-mask-builder.ts** - Optimized Google API update masking
 62: - **event-id-validator.ts** - Event ID format validation
 63: 
 64: ### `src/schemas/`
 65: Zod validation schemas:
 66: - **core.ts** - Calendar event schemas (create, update, recurring)
 67: - **gmail.ts** - Gmail message and filter schemas
 68: - **gmail-label-utils-types.ts** - Label resolution type definitions
 69: - **gmail-batch-types.ts** - Batch operation type definitions
 70: - **email-analyzer-types.ts** - Email categorization type definitions
 71: 
 72: ### `src/testing/`
 73: Test infrastructure:
 74: - **types.ts** - Zod schemas and TypeScript interfaces
 75: - **test-utils.ts** - `withTestContext()`, `typedTest()`, ResourceTracker, cleanup utilities
 76: 
 77: ### `src/tests/`
 78: Test suites:
 79: - **unit/** - Handler, service, and utility tests (486 tests)
 80: - **integration/** - MCP protocol tests with real server and API
 81: 
 82: ### `src/transports/`
 83: MCP transport implementations:
 84: - **stdio.ts** - Standard input/output (Claude Desktop)
 85: - **http.ts** - HTTP server (remote/browser access)
 86: 
 87: ### `src/config/`
 88: - **TransportConfig.ts** - CLI argument parsing (transport type, port, host)
 89: 
 90: ## Key Patterns
 91: 
 92: ### Handler Pattern
 93: ```typescript
 94: class XyzHandler extends BaseToolHandler {
 95:   async execute(input: ParsedInput): Promise<ToolResponse> {
 96:     // Validation via Zod
 97:     // API call via google-auth-library
 98:     // Content assertion via { type: 'text'; text: string }
 99:   }
100: }
101: ```
102: 
103: ### Token Management
104: - Multi-account support via `ACCOUNT_MODE` env var
105: - Auto-refresh 5 min before expiry
106: - Separate storage: Calendar (`tokens.json`) vs Gmail (`tokens-gmail.json`)
107: - Test mode: 7-day expiry (Google requirement)
108: 
109: ### Timezone Handling
110: All datetime operations consolidated in `src/utils/timezone-utils.ts` (refactored ae1c01b, 499e7dd):
111: - `convertToRFC3339()` - Datetime string → RFC3339 with timezone
112: - `convertLocalTimeToUTC()` - Local time + timezone → UTC offset
113: - `hasTimezoneInDatetime()` - Detect timezone in datetime string
114: - `createTimeObject()` - Build datetime object with timezone
115: - Consolidated from multiple datetime utility files for DRY, single source of truth
116: 
117: ### Email Organization Scripts
118: Located in project root (non-MCP):
119: - Uses `lib/gmail-client.mjs` for OAuth
120: - `lib/gmail-label-utils.mjs` for dynamic label ID resolution
121: - `lib/gmail-batch.mjs` for batch operations
122: - `lib/email-analyzer.mjs` for categorization helpers
123: 
124: ## Data Flow
125: 
126: ### Create Event
127: 1. Handler receives input → Zod validation
128: 2. Construct RFC3339 datetime via `timezone-utils`
129: 3. Call `calendar.events.insert()`
130: 4. Check conflicts via `ConflictDetectionService`
131: 5. Return event with MCP tool response format
132: 
133: ### Update Recurring Event
134: 1. Fetch base event → validate recurrence rule
135: 2. Build field mask (only changed fields)
136: 3. For instance modifications: separate start/end times via `RecurringEventHelpers`
137: 4. Apply timezone via `createTimeObject()`
138: 5. Return updated event
139: 
140: ### Search & Filter Gmail
141: 1. Resolve label IDs via `buildLabelCache()` (cached at startup)
142: 2. Construct Gmail search query
143: 3. Fetch message list → fetch details in parallel
144: 4. Apply filters (archive, label, mark read)
145: 5. Use batch API for 10-100x speedup
146: 
147: ## Dependencies
148: - **@modelcontextprotocol/sdk** - MCP protocol
149: - **google-auth-library** - OAuth2, Google API client
150: - **zod** - Schema validation
151: - **vitest** - Testing framework
152: 
153: ## Testing Strategy
154: - **Unit tests (486)** - Handler, service, utility logic isolated
155: - **Integration tests** - Real MCP server spawned, real Google Calendar API
156: - **Schema tests** - Zod validation coverage
157: - **Type-safe assertions** - `{ type: 'text'; text: string }` instead of `as any`
158: 
159: ## Multi-Account Support
160: ```
161: TokenManager
162: ├─ ACCOUNT_MODE=test → test account (7-day expiry)
163: └─ ACCOUNT_MODE=production → prod account (no expiry)
164: ```
165: Token file structure (both accounts in one file):
166: ```json
167: {
168:   "test": { "access_token": "...", "expiry_date": ... },
169:   "production": { "access_token": "...", "expiry_date": ... }
170: }
171: ```
172: 
173: ## Recent Architectural Improvements (v1.4.9+)
174: 
175: ### Auth API Refactoring (c9a57a9)
176: - Replaced direct `validateTokens()` calls with semantic API methods
177: - `isAuthenticated()` - Clearer intent for auth status checks
178: - `getCredentials()` - Improved encapsulation over direct credential access
179: - Applied across 5 locations (server.ts ×2, auth/server.ts ×1, integration tests ×2)
180: - All 486 tests passing after refactor
181: 
182: ### Timezone Utilities Consolidation (ae1c01b, 499e7dd)
183: - Unified all datetime operations into single `src/utils/timezone-utils.ts`
184: - Eliminates code duplication across event creation, update, recurring event handlers
185: - Single source of truth for RFC3339, UTC, and timezone-aware operations
186: - Improved maintainability and consistency
187: 
188: ### Test Infrastructure
189: - 486/486 unit tests covering handlers, services, utilities
190: - Integration tests using real MCP protocol with Google Calendar API
191: - Type-safe content assertions (`{ type: 'text'; text: string }`)
192: - Dynamic future dates prevent test expiration
</file>

<file path="docs/AUTH-REFACTORING-OPPORTUNITIES.md">
  1: # Auth Refactoring Opportunities
  2: 
  3: **Analysis Date:** 2026-03-24
  4: **Goal:** Apply new TokenManager auth methods (`isAuthenticated()`, `getCredentials()`, `refreshCredentials()`, `logout()`) to improve DRY and reduce code duplication.
  5: 
  6: ---
  7: 
  8: ## Executive Summary
  9: 
 10: 3 refactoring opportunities identified:
 11: - **Direct credential access** (1 location) → Use `getCredentials()` method
 12: - **Token validation patterns** (3 locations) → Use `isAuthenticated()` method
 13: - **Verbose token checking** (2 locations) → Simplify with new methods
 14: 
 15: **Estimated Effort:** 15-30 minutes | **Impact:** Cleaner API surface, better encapsulation
 16: 
 17: ---
 18: 
 19: ## Detailed Opportunities
 20: 
 21: ### 1. Direct Credential Access (HIGH PRIORITY)
 22: 
 23: **Location:** `src/verify-tokens.ts:53`
 24: 
 25: **Current Pattern:**
 26: ```typescript
 27: // Direct access to oauth2Client credentials
 28: const credentials = oauth2Client.credentials;
 29: if (credentials.expiry_date) {
 30:   const expiresIn = Math.floor((credentials.expiry_date - Date.now()) / 1000);
 31:   // ... calculate hours/minutes
 32: }
 33: ```
 34: 
 35: **Issue:**
 36: - Direct access to internal `oauth2Client.credentials` violates encapsulation
 37: - Couples verify-tokens.ts to oauth2Client implementation
 38: - No validation that credentials exist
 39: 
 40: **Refactored Pattern:**
 41: ```typescript
 42: // Use TokenManager's new public method
 43: const credentials = tokenManager.getCredentials();
 44: if (credentials?.expiry_date) {
 45:   const expiresIn = Math.floor((credentials.expiry_date - Date.now()) / 1000);
 46:   // ... calculate hours/minutes
 47: }
 48: ```
 49: 
 50: **Benefits:**
 51: - ✅ Encapsulation: oauth2Client.credentials is internal detail
 52: - ✅ Consistency: Use TokenManager for all credential access
 53: - ✅ Safety: null-safe with optional chaining
 54: 
 55: ---
 56: 
 57: ### 2. Token Validation Pattern (MEDIUM PRIORITY)
 58: 
 59: **Locations (3 instances):**
 60: 1. `src/server.ts:61` - `await this.tokenManager.validateTokens(accountMode)`
 61: 2. `src/server.ts:75` - `await this.tokenManager.validateTokens(accountMode)`
 62: 3. `src/auth/server.ts:144` - `await this.tokenManager.validateTokens()`
 63: 
 64: **Current Pattern:**
 65: ```typescript
 66: const hasValidTokens = await this.tokenManager.validateTokens();
 67: if (!hasValidTokens) {
 68:   // handle no auth
 69: }
 70: ```
 71: 
 72: **Refactored Pattern:**
 73: ```typescript
 74: if (!(await this.tokenManager.isAuthenticated())) {
 75:   // handle no auth
 76: }
 77: ```
 78: 
 79: **Benefits:**
 80: - ✅ Intent clarity: `isAuthenticated()` reads better than `validateTokens()`
 81: - ✅ DRY: Semantically correct method name
 82: - ✅ Consistency: All auth checks use `isAuthenticated()`
 83: - ✅ Future-proof: If validation logic changes, only one method to update
 84: 
 85: **Code Impact:**
 86: - `src/server.ts:61` - Rename check and message
 87: - `src/server.ts:75` - Rename check
 88: - `src/auth/server.ts:144` - Rename check
 89: 
 90: ---
 91: 
 92: ### 3. Integration Test Auth Guards (MEDIUM PRIORITY)
 93: 
 94: **Locations (2 instances):**
 95: 1. `src/tests/integration/UpdateEventHandler.recurring.integration.test.ts:32`
 96: 2. `src/tests/integration/conflict-detection-integration.test.ts:31`
 97: 
 98: **Current Pattern:**
 99: ```typescript
100: const hasValidTokens = await tokenManager.validateTokens();
101: if (!hasValidTokens) {
102:   test.skip('No valid tokens from Doppler');
103: }
104: ```
105: 
106: **Refactored Pattern:**
107: ```typescript
108: const isAuth = await tokenManager.isAuthenticated();
109: if (!isAuth) {
110:   test.skip('No valid tokens from Doppler');
111: }
112: ```
113: 
114: **Benefits:**
115: - ✅ Semantic clarity: `isAuthenticated()` is the right method
116: - ✅ Consistency: Test guards use same auth API as production code
117: - ✅ Maintainability: Single semantic meaning across codebase
