  1: # Gmail MCP Tools - Complete Implementation Summary
  2: 
  3: ## Overview
  4: Complete Gmail integration with 5 powerful tools for email search, management, organization, and automation.
  5: 
  6: ---
  7: 
  8: ## ✅ Implementation Status
  9: 
 10: **Date Completed:** 2026-03-23
 11: **Build Status:** ✅ Successful
 12: **Build Size:** 152KB (increased from 144KB)
 13: **All Tools Registered:** ✅ Yes
 14: **Documentation:** ✅ Complete
 15: 
 16: ---
 17: 
 18: ## 5 Gmail Tools Available
 19: 
 20: ### 1. `gmail-search-messages` ✅
 21: Search and retrieve Gmail messages with flexible queries
 22: 
 23: **Key Features:**
 24: - Gmail search syntax support (is:unread, from:, subject:, etc.)
 25: - Pagination support
 26: - Message metadata (subject, from, date, snippet)
 27: - Results estimation
 28: 
 29: **Example:**
 30: ```typescript
 31: const unread = await mcp.callTool('gmail-search-messages', {
 32:   query: 'is:unread AND from:work@company.com',
 33:   maxResults: 50
 34: });
 35: ```
 36: 
 37: ---
 38: 
 39: ### 2. `gmail-get-profile` ✅
 40: Get Gmail account information
 41: 
 42: **Key Features:**
 43: - Email address
 44: - Total message count
 45: - Total thread count
 46: - Quick account overview
 47: 
 48: **Example:**
 49: ```typescript
 50: const profile = await mcp.callTool('gmail-get-profile');
 51: console.log(`Emails: ${profile.messagesTotal}`);
 52: ```
 53: 
 54: ---
 55: 
 56: ### 3. `gmail-modify-messages` ✅
 57: Modify emails in batch operations
 58: 
 59: **Supported Actions:**
 60: - `markRead` - Mark as read
 61: - `markUnread` - Mark as unread
 62: - `archive` - Move to archive
 63: - `delete` - Permanently delete
 64: - `addLabel` - Add label(s)
 65: - `removeLabel` - Remove label(s)
 66: 
 67: **Example:**
 68: ```typescript
 69: const result = await mcp.callTool('gmail-modify-messages', {
 70:   messageIds: ['id1', 'id2', 'id3'],
 71:   action: 'archive'
 72: });
 73: console.log(`Archived: ${result.processed}`);
 74: ```
 75: 
 76: ---
 77: 
 78: ### 4. `gmail-create-label` ✅ **NEW**
 79: Create Gmail labels for organization
 80: 
 81: **Key Features:**
 82: - Create new labels with custom names
 83: - Control visibility in label list
 84: - Control visibility in message list
 85: - Returns label ID for reference
 86: 
 87: **Example:**
 88: ```typescript
 89: const label = await mcp.callTool('gmail-create-label', {
 90:   name: 'ClientProjects',
 91:   labelListVisibility: 'labelShow',
 92:   messageListVisibility: 'show'
 93: });
 94: console.log(`Created label: ${label.label.id}`);
 95: ```
 96: 
 97: **Label Visibility Options:**
 98: - `labelShow` (visible in list) / `labelHide` (hidden)
 99: - `show` (visible with messages) / `hide` (hidden from list)
100: 
101: ---
102: 
103: ### 5. `gmail-create-filter` ✅ **NEW**
104: Create filters for automatic email organization
105: 
106: **Criteria Matching:**
107: - `from` - Sender email
108: - `to` - Recipient email
109: - `subject` - Subject line
110: - `query` - Gmail search query
111: - `hasAttachment` - Email has attachments
112: - `excludeChats` - Exclude chat messages
113: 
114: **Auto-Actions:**
115: - `addLabelIds` - Automatically label
116: - `removeLabelIds` - Remove labels
117: - `archive` - Auto-archive
118: - `markAsRead` - Mark as read
119: - `markAsSpam` - Mark as spam
120: - `markAsTrash` - Move to trash
121: - `forward` - Forward to email
122: - `neverMarkAsSpam` - Train filter
123: 
124: **Example:**
125: ```typescript
126: const filter = await mcp.callTool('gmail-create-filter', {
127:   criteria: {
128:     from: 'newsletter@example.com'
129:   },
130:   action: {
131:     archive: true,
132:     markAsRead: true
133:   }
134: });
135: ```
136: 
137: ---
138: 
139: ## Complete Workflow Examples
140: 
141: ### Complete Email Organization Setup
142: ```typescript
143: // 1. Create labels
144: const workLabel = await mcp.callTool('gmail-create-label', {
145:   name: 'Work',
146:   labelListVisibility: 'labelShow'
147: });
148: 
149: const invoiceLabel = await mcp.callTool('gmail-create-label', {
150:   name: 'Invoices',
151:   labelListVisibility: 'labelShow'
152: });
153: 
154: // 2. Create filters for automatic organization
155: await mcp.callTool('gmail-create-filter', {
156:   criteria: { from: 'work@company.com' },
157:   action: { addLabelIds: [workLabel.label.id] }
158: });
159: 
160: await mcp.callTool('gmail-create-filter', {
161:   criteria: { subject: 'invoice' },
162:   action: {
163:     addLabelIds: [invoiceLabel.label.id],
164:     archive: true,
165:     markAsRead: true
166:   }
167: });
168: 
169: // 3. Organize existing emails
170: const workEmails = await mcp.callTool('gmail-search-messages', {
171:   query: 'from:work@company.com',
172:   maxResults: 100
173: });
174: 
175: await mcp.callTool('gmail-modify-messages', {
176:   action: 'addLabel',
177:   messageIds: workEmails.messages.map(m => m.id),
178:   labelId: workLabel.label.id
179: });
180: 
181: console.log('✅ Complete email organization setup!');
182: ```
183: 
184: ### Smart Inbox Management
185: ```typescript
186: // Get account status
187: const profile = await mcp.callTool('gmail-get-profile');
188: console.log(`Total emails: ${profile.messagesTotal}`);
189: 
190: // Find and organize newsletters
191: const newsletters = await mcp.callTool('gmail-search-messages', {
192:   query: 'is:unread AND (from:newsletter OR from:updates OR label:Promotions)',
193:   maxResults: 100
194: });
195: 
196: // Create newsletter label
197: const newsLabel = await mcp.callTool('gmail-create-label', {
198:   name: 'Newsletters',
199:   labelListVisibility: 'labelHide'
200: });
201: 
202: // Archive old newsletters
203: const oldNewsletters = await mcp.callTool('gmail-search-messages', {
204:   query: 'label:Promotions before:2026-03-01',
205:   maxResults: 100
206: });
207: 
208: await mcp.callTool('gmail-modify-messages', {
209:   action: 'archive',
210:   messageIds: oldNewsletters.messages.map(m => m.id)
211: });
212: 
213: // Create filter for future newsletters
214: await mcp.callTool('gmail-create-filter', {
215:   criteria: {
216:     query: 'from:newsletter OR from:updates'
217:   },
218:   action: {
219:     addLabelIds: [newsLabel.label.id],
220:     archive: true
221:   }
222: });
223: 
224: console.log('✅ Smart inbox management complete!');
225: ```
226: 
