  1: # Gmail MCP Tools Guide
  2: 
  3: ## Overview
  4: Three comprehensive Gmail tools are now available in the MCP server for searching, reading, and modifying email messages.
  5: 
  6: ---
  7: 
  8: ## Available Tools
  9: 
 10: ### Overview
 11: Five comprehensive Gmail tools for searching, managing, organizing, and automating email workflows.
 12: 
 13: ---
 14: 
 15: ### 1. `gmail-search-messages`
 16: Search and retrieve Gmail messages with flexible query support.
 17: 
 18: **Parameters:**
 19: - `query` (required, string): Gmail search query
 20:   - Examples: `is:unread`, `from:user@example.com`, `subject:hello`, `has:attachment`
 21:   - Can combine: `is:unread AND from:work@company.com`
 22: - `maxResults` (optional, 1-100): Number of messages to return (default: 10)
 23: - `pageToken` (optional, string): Token for pagination to get next batch
 24: 
 25: **Response:**
 26: ```json
 27: {
 28:   "total": 201,
 29:   "returned": 10,
 30:   "messages": [
 31:     {
 32:       "id": "msg_id_123",
 33:       "threadId": "thread_id_456",
 34:       "snippet": "Message preview text...",
 35:       "subject": "Email Subject",
 36:       "from": "sender@example.com",
 37:       "date": "2026-03-23T10:30:00Z"
 38:     }
 39:   ],
 40:   "nextPageToken": "CAIQAA..."
 41: }
 42: ```
 43: 
 44: **Common Queries:**
 45: - `is:unread` - All unread messages
 46: - `from:user@example.com` - From specific sender
 47: - `subject:keyword` - Messages with keyword in subject
 48: - `has:attachment` - Messages with attachments
 49: - `is:starred` - Starred messages
 50: - `label:work` - Messages with label
 51: - `before:2026-03-20` - Messages before date
 52: - `after:2026-03-20` - Messages after date
 53: 
 54: ---
 55: 
 56: ### 2. `gmail-get-profile`
 57: Get summary information about the Gmail account.
 58: 
 59: **Parameters:** None
 60: 
 61: **Response:**
 62: ```json
 63: {
 64:   "emailAddress": "user@gmail.com",
 65:   "messagesTotal": 5432,
 66:   "threadsTotal": 2156,
 67:   "historyId": "67890"
 68: }
 69: ```
 70: 
 71: **Use Cases:**
 72: - Quick account overview
 73: - Check total message count
 74: - Verify authenticated email
 75: 
 76: ---
 77: 
 78: ### 3. `gmail-modify-messages`
 79: Modify Gmail messages in batch: mark read/unread, archive, delete, manage labels.
 80: 
 81: **Parameters:**
 82: - `messageIds` (required, array): Array of message IDs (at least 1)
 83: - `action` (required, enum): Action to perform
 84:   - `markRead` - Mark messages as read
 85:   - `markUnread` - Mark messages as unread
 86:   - `archive` - Move to archive (remove from inbox)
 87:   - `delete` - Permanently delete messages
 88:   - `addLabel` - Add a label (requires labelId)
 89:   - `removeLabel` - Remove a label (requires labelId)
 90: - `labelId` (optional, string): Gmail label ID (required for label operations)
 91: 
 92: **Response:**
 93: ```json
 94: {
 95:   "action": "markRead",
 96:   "processed": 5,
 97:   "failed": 0,
 98:   "messages": [
 99:     {
100:       "id": "msg_id_1",
101:       "action": "marked as read",
102:       "success": true
103:     },
104:     {
105:       "id": "msg_id_2",
106:       "action": "marked as read",
107:       "success": true
108:     }
109:   ]
110: }
111: ```
112: 
113: **Action Details:**
114: 
115: #### Mark as Read
116: ```
117: action: "markRead"
118: messageIds: ["id1", "id2", "id3"]
119: ```
120: - Removes UNREAD label
121: - Message no longer appears in unread count
122: 
123: #### Mark as Unread
124: ```
125: action: "markUnread"
126: messageIds: ["id1", "id2"]
127: ```
128: - Adds UNREAD label
129: - Appears in unread messages again
130: 
131: #### Archive
132: ```
133: action: "archive"
134: messageIds: ["id1", "id2"]
135: ```
136: - Removes from INBOX
137: - Still searchable and in All Mail
138: - No longer appears in inbox
139: 
140: #### Delete
141: ```
142: action: "delete"
143: messageIds: ["id1", "id2"]
144: ```
145: - Permanently deletes messages
146: - Messages moved to Trash (can be recovered briefly)
147: - Eventually purged from Google servers
148: 
149: #### Add Label
150: ```
151: action: "addLabel"
152: messageIds: ["id1", "id2"]
153: labelId: "Label_123"  // Required!
154: ```
155: - Applies label to messages
156: - Messages can have multiple labels
157: - Use gmail-get-labels to find label IDs (if available)
158: 
159: #### Remove Label
160: ```
161: action: "removeLabel"
162: messageIds: ["id1", "id2"]
163: labelId: "Label_123"  // Required!
164: ```
165: - Removes label from messages
166: - Does not delete message
167: - Message still exists with other labels
168: 
169: ---
170: 
171: ### 4. `gmail-create-label`
172: Create new Gmail labels for organizing and categorizing emails.
173: 
174: **Parameters:**
175: - `name` (required, string): Label name
176:   - Examples: "Work", "Personal", "Invoices", "Follow Up"
177:   - Cannot contain special characters
178: - `labelListVisibility` (optional, enum): Show/hide in label list
179:   - `labelShow` - Visible in label list (default)
180:   - `labelHide` - Hidden from label list
181: - `messageListVisibility` (optional, enum): Show/hide in message list
182:   - `show` - Appears when message has label (default)
183:   - `hide` - Hidden from message list
184: 
185: **Response:**
186: ```json
187: {
188:   "success": true,
189:   "label": {
190:     "id": "Label_1234567890",
191:     "name": "Work",
192:     "messageCount": 0,
193:     "threadCount": 0,
194:     "labelListVisibility": "labelShow",
195:     "messageListVisibility": "show"
196:   },
197:   "message": "Label \"Work\" created successfully"
198: }
199: ```
200: 
201: **Use Cases:**
202: - Create organizational labels (Work, Personal, Invoices, etc.)
203: - Create workflow labels (TODO, Follow Up, Waiting For, etc.)
204: - Create category labels (Receipts, Contracts, etc.)
205: 
206: **Error Handling:**
207: ```json
208: {
209:   "success": false,
210:   "error": "Label \"Work\" already exists",
211:   "suggestion": "Use a different name or try to find the existing label"
212: }
213: ```
214: 
215: ---
216: 
217: ### 5. `gmail-create-filter`
218: Create filters to automatically organize incoming emails based on matching criteria.
219: 
220: **Parameters:**
221: - `criteria` (required, object): Matching conditions
222:   - `from` (optional, string): Filter emails from specific sender
223:   - `to` (optional, string): Filter emails to specific recipient
224:   - `subject` (optional, string): Filter by subject line
225:   - `query` (optional, string): Gmail search query
226:   - `hasAttachment` (optional, boolean): Only emails with attachments
227:   - `excludeChats` (optional, boolean): Exclude chat messages
228: 
229: - `action` (required, object): Actions to apply
230:   - `addLabelIds` (optional, array): Labels to automatically add
231:   - `removeLabelIds` (optional, array): Labels to automatically remove
232:   - `archive` (optional, boolean): Auto-archive matching emails
233:   - `markAsRead` (optional, boolean): Auto-mark as read
234:   - `markAsSpam` (optional, boolean): Auto-mark as spam
235:   - `markAsTrash` (optional, boolean): Auto-move to trash
236:   - `forward` (optional, string): Forward to email address
237:   - `neverMarkAsSpam` (optional, boolean): Never mark as spam
238: 
239: **Response:**
240: ```json
241: {
242:   "success": true,
243:   "filter": {
244:     "id": "AAAAAAA",
245:     "criteria": {
246:       "from": "newsletter@example.com"
247:     },
248:     "action": {
249:       "addLabelIds": ["Label_123"],
250:       "skip": true
251:     }
252:   },
253:   "message": "Filter created successfully",
254:   "summary": "Filter: IF (from: newsletter@example.com) THEN archive, add 1 label(s)"
255: }
256: ```
257: 
258: **Filter Examples:**
259: 
260: #### Newsletter Auto-Archive
261: ```json
262: {
263:   "criteria": {
264:     "from": "newsletter@example.com"
265:   },
266:   "action": {
267:     "archive": true
268:   }
269: }
270: ```
271: - All emails from newsletter automatically archived
272: - Won't appear in inbox
273: 
274: #### Invoice Auto-Label and Archive
275: ```json
276: {
277:   "criteria": {
278:     "subject": "invoice"
279:   },
280:   "action": {
281:     "addLabelIds": ["Label_Invoices"],
282:     "archive": true
283:   }
284: }
285: ```
286: - Emails with "invoice" in subject get labeled
287: - Automatically archived from inbox
288: 
289: #### Work Email Auto-Organization
290: ```json
291: {
292:   "criteria": {
293:     "from": "work@company.com"
294:   },
295:   "action": {
296:     "addLabelIds": ["Label_Work"],
297:     "markAsRead": false
298:   }
299: }
300: ```
301: - Auto-label work emails
302: - Keeps them unread for attention
303: 
304: #### Spam Prevention Filter
305: ```json
306: {
307:   "criteria": {
308:     "from": "spam@example.com"
309:   },
310:   "action": {
311:     "markAsSpam": true
312:   }
313: }
314: ```
315: - Automatically mark as spam
316: - Train Gmail's spam filter
317: 
318: #### Forward Receipts
319: ```json
320: {
321:   "criteria": {
322:     "subject": "receipt"
323:   },
324:   "action": {
325:     "forward": "accounting@company.com",
326:     "addLabelIds": ["Label_Receipts"]
327:   }
328: }
329: ```
330: - Forward receipts to accounting
331: - Keep copy with label
332: 
333: #### Attachment Auto-Organize
334: ```json
335: {
336:   "criteria": {
337:     "hasAttachment": true,
338:     "from": "clients@external.com"
339:   },
340:   "action": {
341:     "addLabelIds": ["Label_ClientDocuments"]
342:   }
343: }
344: ```
345: - Auto-label emails with attachments from clients
346: - Easy to find important documents
347: 
