383: ---
384: 
385: ## Gmail Label IDs
386: 
387: Standard Gmail labels use predefined IDs:
388: - `INBOX` - Inbox
389: - `SENT` - Sent Mail
390: - `DRAFT` - Drafts
391: - `UNREAD` - Unread messages
392: - `STARRED` - Starred messages
393: - `TRASH` - Trash/Bin
394: - `SPAM` - Spam
395: 
396: Custom labels have unique IDs starting with `Label_` (e.g., `Label_1234567890`)
397: 
398: To find custom label IDs, you would typically need a separate `gmail-get-labels` tool (future enhancement).
399: 
400: ---
401: 
402: ## Error Handling
403: 
404: ### Missing Required Parameters
405: ```json
406: {
407:   "error": "labelId required for addLabel action"
408: }
409: ```
410: 
411: ### Invalid Message IDs
412: ```json
413: {
414:   "id": "invalid_id",
415:   "action": "markRead",
416:   "success": false,
417:   "error": "Not Found"
418: }
419: ```
420: 
421: ### Batch Partial Failures
422: ```json
423: {
424:   "action": "delete",
425:   "processed": 3,
426:   "failed": 1,
427:   "messages": [
428:     { "id": "id1", "success": true },
429:     { "id": "id2", "success": true },
430:     { "id": "id3", "success": false, "error": "Not Found" }
431:   ]
432: }
433: ```
434: 
435: ---
436: 
437: ## Permissions & Security
438: 
439: **OAuth Scopes Required:**
440: - `gmail.readonly` - For search and profile operations
441: - `gmail.modify` - For modification operations (marking, archiving, deleting, labels)
442: 
443: **Important Notes:**
444: - Operations are performed on authenticated user's account
445: - Cannot modify emails in other users' accounts
446: - Deleted emails are recoverable from Trash for ~30 days
447: - Modifications are logged in Gmail audit trail
448: - Batch operations are atomic per message (one fails doesn't stop others)
449: 
450: ---
451: 
452: ## Rate Limiting
453: 
454: Gmail API has rate limits:
455: - 250 quota units per user per second
456: - Each message operation: ~1 unit
457: - Search operations: ~1-5 units depending on query complexity
458: - Profile: ~1 unit
459: 
460: Batch operations are recommended to stay within limits (modify many messages in one call vs many separate calls).
461: 
