116: ### Multi-Account Support (Test Mode)
117: 
118: This server supports multiple Google accounts in test mode with automatic token management.
119: 
120: **Setup both accounts:**
121: 
122: Account 1 (Initial):
123: ```bash
124: export ACCOUNT_MODE=test
125: export CALENDARMCP_TOKEN_PATH=~/.config/google-calendar-mcp/tokens.json
126: npm run auth
127: ```
128: 
129: Account 2 (Same file, different account key):
130: ```bash
131: export ACCOUNT_MODE=test
132: export CALENDARMCP_TOKEN_PATH=~/.config/google-calendar-mcp/tokens.json
133: npm run auth  # Authenticates second account in same tokens.json
134: ```
135: 
136: **Verify both accounts:**
137: ```bash
138: export GOOGLE_OAUTH_CREDENTIALS="./credentials.json"
139: npm run verify-tokens
140: ```
141: 
142: Outputs token status, expiry times, and account validity for all authenticated accounts.
143: 
144: **Important Notes:**
145: - Both accounts stored in single `tokens.json` file with separate keys
146: - Tokens expire after 7 days in test mode (Google requirement)
147: - TokenManager auto-refreshes tokens 5 minutes before expiry
148: - Set `ACCOUNT_MODE` environment variable before running the server to select which account is active
