150: ### Re-authentication
151: 
152: If you're in test mode (default), tokens expire after 7 days. If you are using a client like Claude Desktop it should open up a browser window to automatically re-auth. However, if you see authentication errors you can also resolve by following these steps:
153: 
154: **For npx users:**
155: ```bash
156: export GOOGLE_OAUTH_CREDENTIALS="/path/to/your/gcp-oauth.keys.json"
157: export ACCOUNT_MODE=test
158: npx @cocal/google-calendar-mcp auth
159: ```
160: 
161: **For local installation:**
162: ```bash
163: export ACCOUNT_MODE=test
164: npm run auth
165: ```
166: 
167: **To avoid weekly re-authentication**, publish your app to production mode (without verification):
168: 1. Go to Google Cloud Console → "APIs & Services" → "OAuth consent screen"
169: 2. Click "PUBLISH APP" and confirm
170: 3. Your tokens will no longer expire after 7 days but Google will show a more threatning warning when connecting to the app about it being unverified.
