115: ## Dependencies: Replace Custom Batch Chunking with p-limit
116: 
117: **Status:** ✅ Done
118: **Complexity:** Low
119: **Impact:** Low–Medium (cleaner concurrency control)
120: **Discovery Date:** 2026-03-25
121: 
122: **Opportunity:**
123: `src/utils/batchProcessor.ts` implements parallel batch processing with manual chunking:
124: - `processBatchItems()` — Already uses `Promise.all()` (no concurrency limit)
125: - `processBatchItemsChunked()` — Manual loop chunking to control parallelism
126: 
127: The `p-limit` library (3KB) or `p-queue` (8KB) can replace the chunking logic cleanly.
128: 
129: **Current Implementation:**
130: ```typescript
131: // Lines 106–136: Manual slice/chunk loop
132: for (let chunkIndex = 0; chunkIndex < items.length; chunkIndex += batchSize) {
133:   const chunk = items.slice(chunkIndex, chunkIndex + batchSize);
134:   const promises = chunk.map(item => operation(item));
135:   const outcomes = await Promise.all(promises);
136:   // ... error handling
137: }
138: ```
139: 
140: **Replacement with p-limit:**
141: ```typescript
142: import pLimit from 'p-limit';
143: 
144: const limit = pLimit(batchSize);
145: const promises = items.map(item => limit(() => operation(item)));
146: const outcomes = await Promise.all(promises);
147: ```
148: 
149: **Scope:**
150: 1. Add `p-limit` to dependencies: `npm install p-limit`
151: 2. Refactor `processBatchItemsChunked()`:
152:    - Remove manual `for` loop (10+ lines)
153:    - Use `pLimit` to control concurrency
154:    - Keep error aggregation logic
155: 3. Consider simplifying `processBatchItems()` to always use p-limit with max concurrency
156: 4. Update callers: None expected (internal utility); test thoroughly
157: 
158: **Files Affected:**
159: - `src/utils/batchProcessor.ts` — Simplify chunking logic (~15 LOC saved)
160: - `package.json` — Add p-limit dependency
